Headlines.Author: Nathalie Tadena
Headlines.Headline: TE Connectivity 3Q Net Up 8%, Raises Full-Year Outlook

PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES TE Connectivity Ltd.'s TEL fiscal third-quarter profit rose 7.6% as the top line got a boost from acquisitions and strength in the communications and industrial-solutions segment, offsetting higher costs. Formerly Tyco Electronics, the maker of electronics components for automobiles and consumer devices also raised its full-year earnings guidance, saying it now expects earnings of $3.06 to $3.10 on sales of $14.3 billion to $14.4 billion. In April, the company had lowered its estimate to $2.95 to $3.07 earnings a share and raised the bottom end of its revenue growth range, to $14 billion to $14.3 billion.
